- `interpolator x y(t)` is a function from `ℝ` to `E n`.
- `interpolated x y f(t) = f(interpolator x y(t))`.

So, by the chain rule:
`deriv (interpolated x y f) (t) = ∑ i, (nth_partial i f) (interpolator x y(t)) * (deriv (interpolator x y) (t) i)`

